import React, { useState } from 'react'; const AnalyticsTable = () => { // Initialize state for storing filter values for each column const [filters, setFilters] = useState({ location: '', ipAddress: '', qrCodeId: '', scanTime: '', referenceUrl: '', browser: '', deviceType: '', operatingSystem: '', userRepeatFrequency: '' }); // Sample data for table rows const rows = [ { location: "New York, USA", ipAddress: "192.168.0.1", qrCodeId: "QR12345", scanTime: "2024-11-08 10:30 AM", referenceUrl: "www.example.com/scan", browser: "Chrome", deviceType: "Mobile", operatingSystem: "Android 13", userRepeatFrequency: "Once" }, { location: "London, UK", ipAddress: "203.0.113.5", qrCodeId: "QR67890", scanTime: "2024-11-08 11:15 AM", referenceUrl: "www.example.com/scan", browser: "Safari", deviceType: "Desktop", operatingSystem: "macOS 12", userRepeatFrequency: "Twice" } // Add more rows as needed ]; // Function to update filter values based on user input const handleFilterChange = (column, value) => { setFilters({ ...filters, [column]: value.toLowerCase() }); }; // Function to filter rows based on column filters const filteredRows = rows.filter(row => { return ( row.location.toLowerCase().includes(filters.location) && row.ipAddress.toLowerCase().includes(filters.ipAddress) && row.qrCodeId.toLowerCase().includes(filters.qrCodeId) && row.scanTime.toLowerCase().includes(filters.scanTime) && row.referenceUrl.toLowerCase().includes(filters.referenceUrl) && row.browser.toLowerCase().includes(filters.browser) && row.deviceType.toLowerCase().includes(filters.deviceType) && row.operatingSystem.toLowerCase().includes(filters.operatingSystem) && row.userRepeatFrequency.toLowerCase().includes(filters.userRepeatFrequency) ); }); return (
{/* Filter Input Fields */} {filteredRows.map((row, index) => ( ))}
